# PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)
# AI Chatbot Application
# Version: 1.0
# Date: 2026-04-09
# Status: Draft

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## 1. OVERVIEW

### 1.1 Product Summary
A powerful, minimal, dark-themed AI chatbot web application that mirrors the
experience of ChatGPT. Users interact with an AI assistant powered by a
user-supplied API key. The bot answers questions across all general domains
(coding, writing, math, analysis, creative tasks, etc.). When the AI cannot
confidently answer a query, it gracefully redirects the user to a curated
external resource or web search so the user can find the answer themselves.

### 1.2 Vision Statement
"Give every user a personal AI assistant — fast, smart, honest about its
limits, and always helpful — wrapped in a clean, distraction-free dark UI."

### 1.3 Goals
- Replicate the core conversational experience of ChatGPT.
- Allow any developer / user to plug in their own AI API key (OpenAI,
  Anthropic, Gemini, or any OpenAI-compatible endpoint).
- Surface a clean, minimal, dark-mode interface by default.
- Automatically detect when a question is out of scope or unanswerable and
  redirect users to trusted external resources.
- Be fully self-hostable with zero mandatory backend (pure frontend + API).

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## 2. TARGET USERS

| User Type          | Description                                                  |
|--------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| General Public     | People who want ChatGPT-like answers without a subscription. |
| Developers         | Builders who want to embed AI chat into their own projects.  |
| Students           | Learners seeking explanations, tutoring, and research help.  |
| Small Businesses   | Teams that want an internal AI assistant with their own key. |

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## 3. CORE FEATURES

### 3.1 API Key Configuration
- On first launch, a modal/settings panel prompts the user to enter their API key.
- Supported providers:
    • OpenAI          → https://api.openai.com/v1
    • Anthropic       → https://api.anthropic.com/v1
    • Google Gemini   → https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com
    • Custom endpoint → user-defined base URL (OpenAI-compatible)
- The key is stored in localStorage (never sent to any third-party server).
- A dropdown lets the user select the model (e.g., gpt-4o, claude-sonnet-4,
  gemini-2.5-pro).
- Users can update or revoke their API key at any time from the Settings panel.

### 3.2 Conversational Chat Interface
- Input box at the bottom of the screen (same as ChatGPT).
- Send on Enter key or click of Send button.
- Supports Shift+Enter for multi-line input.
- Messages rendered in a scrollable chat window.
- Each message shows:
    • User avatar / AI avatar (minimal icon).
    • Sender label ("You" / "Assistant").
    • Timestamp (optional, togglable).
    • Message content with full Markdown rendering.
- AI responses streamed token-by-token (streaming API calls) so the user sees
  output appear in real time.
- "Stop generating" button appears during streaming.
- Auto-scroll to the latest message.

### 3.3 Markdown & Code Rendering
- Full Markdown support: headings, bold, italic, lists, tables, blockquotes.
- Code blocks with:
    • Syntax highlighting (using highlight.js or Prism.js).
    • Language label (e.g., "python", "javascript").
    • One-click "Copy" button on every code block.
- Math rendering via KaTeX (LaTeX expressions between $...$ or $$...$$).
- Inline code styled distinctly from prose.

### 3.4 Conversation Management (Sidebar)
- Left sidebar (collapsible) lists all past conversations.
- Each conversation entry shows:
    • Auto-generated title (first user message, truncated to ~40 chars).
    • Date of last message.
- Actions per conversation:
    • Rename
    • Delete
    • Pin to top
- "New Chat" button at the top of the sidebar.
- Conversations persisted in localStorage (no backend required).
- Export conversation as:
    • Plain text (.txt)
    • Markdown (.md)
    • JSON

### 3.5 System Prompt / Persona Configuration
- "System Prompt" field in Settings allows the user to define the AI's persona,
  tone, language, and behavior.
- Default system prompt (see Section 6 — Master AI Prompt).
- The system prompt is prepended to every conversation invisibly.
- Presets dropdown: "General Assistant", "Coding Expert", "Writing Coach",
  "Math Tutor", "Customer Support Agent" (user can add custom presets).

### 3.6 Fallback & Redirect Logic (KEY FEATURE)
When the AI cannot answer, instead of hallucinating or saying only "I don't
know", the app:

  STEP 1 — AI signals uncertainty using a structured JSON response flag:
           { "can_answer": false, "topic": "<topic>", "query": "<user query>" }

  STEP 2 — Frontend detects the flag and shows a "Could not answer" card.

  STEP 3 — The card displays 3–5 curated redirect links:

    Tier 1 — Direct knowledge sources:
      • Wikipedia                → https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?search=<query>
      • Khan Academy             → https://www.khanacademy.org/search?page_search_query=<query>
      • Stack Overflow           → https://stackoverflow.com/search?q=<query>
      • MDN Web Docs             → https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/search?q=<query>
      • arXiv (research papers)  → https://arxiv.org/search/?query=<query>

    Tier 2 — General search:
      • Google Search            → https://www.google.com/search?q=<query>
      • DuckDuckGo               → https://duckduckgo.com/?q=<query>
      • Bing                     → https://www.bing.com/search?q=<query>

    Topic-based routing:
      • Coding questions         → Stack Overflow + GitHub Search + MDN
      • Medical questions        → WebMD + Mayo Clinic + NIH
      • Legal questions          → FindLaw + LexisNexis
      • News/current events      → Google News + Reuters
      • Math/science             → Wolfram Alpha + Khan Academy
      • Academic research        → Google Scholar + arXiv + JSTOR

  STEP 4 — Each redirect link opens in a new tab.
  STEP 5 — Conversation continues normally after the redirect card.

### 3.7 Smart Suggestions
- After each AI response, 3 follow-up question chips are shown (AI-generated).
- Clicking a chip auto-fills the input and sends the message.
- Can be toggled off in Settings.

### 3.8 Voice Input (Optional / Phase 2)
- Microphone button next to the text input.
- Uses Web Speech API (browser-native, no extra API cost).
- Transcribed text populates the input box.
- User reviews and sends manually.

### 3.9 File / Image Upload (Optional / Phase 2)
- Drag-and-drop or click-to-upload files into the chat.
- Supported for API providers that support vision (e.g., GPT-4o, Claude 3.x).
- Inline image preview before sending.
- PDF text extraction (via pdf.js) for text-only models.

