## 4. UI / UX DESIGN SPECIFICATION

### 4.1 Design Philosophy
- Minimal. Dark. Fast.
- No decorative clutter. Every element must serve a purpose.
- Inspired by ChatGPT's layout but cleaner and more open.

### 4.2 Color Palette (Dark Mode — Default)

  Background (main chat area):   #0d0d0d   (near black)
  Background (sidebar):          #171717   (dark grey)
  Background (input area):       #1e1e1e
  Surface / Card background:     #262626
  Border / Divider:              #2e2e2e
  Primary accent:                #10a37f   (ChatGPT-style teal/green)
  Secondary accent:              #5436da   (purple, for links / highlights)
  Text (primary):                #ececec
  Text (secondary / muted):      #8e8ea0
  Text (code):                   #e06c75
  User message bubble:           #1a1a2e   (slightly blue-dark)
  AI message bubble:             transparent (uses main background)
  Error color:                   #ef4444
  Warning color:                 #f59e0b
  Success color:                 #22c55e

### 4.3 Typography
  Font family:     "Inter", "Söhne", sans-serif (fallback: system-ui)
  Chat font size:  15–16px
  Code font:       "JetBrains Mono", "Fira Code", monospace
  Line height:     1.65 (for readability)

### 4.4 Layout Structure

  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  [≡] LOGO / APP NAME              [Settings ⚙] [New Chat ✚]   │  ← Top bar
  ├──────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │              │                                                  │
  │   SIDEBAR    │              CHAT AREA                          │
  │              │                                                  │
  │ [+ New Chat] │   ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
  │              │   │  AI Avatar  Message text here...          │  │
  │ Past chats:  │   │            with markdown rendering         │  │
  │  • Chat 1    │   └──────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
  │  • Chat 2    │                                                  │
  │  • Chat 3    │   ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
  │  ...         │   │  You      Your message text here...       │  │
  │              │   └──────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
  │              │                                                  │
  │              │   [Suggested follow-up chips]                   │
  │              │                                                  │
  ├──────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │   [ 🎙 ]  [ Type your message here...              ] [ ➤ Send ] │  ← Input bar
  │             Model: gpt-4o ▾      Tokens used: 1,240            │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

### 4.5 Responsive Behavior
- Desktop (>1024px): Sidebar always visible, chat takes remaining width.
- Tablet (768–1024px): Sidebar hidden by default, toggle with hamburger icon.
- Mobile (<768px): Full-screen chat, sidebar is a slide-in drawer.
- Input bar always pinned to bottom of viewport.

### 4.6 Animations
- Messages fade in smoothly (opacity 0→1, translateY 8px→0, 200ms ease).
- Streaming text appears character-by-character (no janky jumps).
- Sidebar slides in/out (300ms ease-in-out).
- Loading dots (3-dot bounce) shown while waiting for first token.
- All transitions respect `prefers-reduced-motion` media query.

### 4.7 Accessibility
- All interactive elements keyboard-navigable.
- ARIA labels on icon-only buttons.
- Focus ring visible on all focusable elements.
- Contrast ratios ≥ 4.5:1 for all text on backgrounds.
- Screen-reader-friendly message list with role="log" and aria-live="polite".

