## 5. TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE

### 5.1 Stack
  Frontend:    React 18 + TypeScript
  Styling:     Tailwind CSS (dark mode configured)
  Build tool:  Vite
  State:       Zustand (lightweight global store)
  Storage:     localStorage (conversations, settings, API key)
  Deployment:  Static hosting (Vercel, Netlify, GitHub Pages, or self-hosted)

### 5.2 API Integration Layer

  File: /src/lib/apiClient.ts

  - Abstracts all AI provider calls behind a single `sendMessage()` function.
  - Accepts:
      • provider: "openai" | "anthropic" | "gemini" | "custom"
      • model: string
      • apiKey: string
      • messages: Message[]
      • systemPrompt: string
      • stream: boolean
  - Returns: AsyncGenerator<string> (token stream) or Promise<string>.
  - Handles:
      • 401 Unauthorized → show "Invalid API Key" toast.
      • 429 Rate Limit   → show "Rate limit hit, slow down" toast with retry countdown.
      • 500 Server Error → show "AI provider error" toast.
      • Network timeout  → show "Connection timeout" toast.

### 5.3 Fallback Detection Logic

  File: /src/lib/fallbackDetector.ts

  - After receiving the AI response, run through:
      1. Check if AI explicitly says it cannot answer (keyword detection).
      2. Check confidence score if the model provides one.
      3. Check if the structured JSON flag { "can_answer": false } is present.
  - If fallback triggered:
      • Parse the topic from the AI's structured response.
      • Map the topic to a redirect category (coding, medical, legal, etc.).
      • Return an array of 3–5 redirect objects: { label, url, icon }.
  - The system prompt (Section 6) instructs the AI to always return the
    structured JSON flag when it cannot answer.

### 5.4 Data Models

  Message:
    id: string (uuid)
    role: "user" | "assistant" | "system"
    content: string
    timestamp: number
    isStreaming?: boolean
    fallback?: FallbackData

  FallbackData:
    triggered: boolean
    topic: string
    redirects: Redirect[]

  Redirect:
    label: string
    url: string
    icon: string (emoji or icon name)
    category: string

  Conversation:
    id: string (uuid)
    title: string
    messages: Message[]
    createdAt: number
    updatedAt: number
    pinned: boolean
    model: string
    systemPrompt: string

  Settings:
    apiKey: string (encrypted in localStorage)
    provider: ProviderType
    model: string
    systemPrompt: string
    theme: "dark" | "light" | "system"
    streamingEnabled: boolean
    suggestionsEnabled: boolean
    fontSize: "sm" | "md" | "lg"

